index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..19b99cb621481ee769cd6fed8fb0470143d0fb6f
--- /dev/null
+++ a/assets/luts/kodak/NOTICE.md
@@ -0,0 +1,19 @@
+# Included Film-Look LUTs
+
+The `.cube` files in this directory are original UVSR simulations authored for
+the AgX Base working space. They are not measurements, official LUTs, or exact
+emulations of any photographic product.
+
+The looks use these manufacturer-published characteristics as creative
+references:
+
+- **2383 Print** — rich blacks, neutral highlights, and a theatrical print-film
+  tone scale. Reference: https://www.kodak.com/en/motion/product/post/print-films/vision-color-2383-3383/
+- **Portra 400** — smooth, natural skin-tone reproduction with strong color
+  saturation over varied lighting. Reference: https://kodakprofessional.com/photographers/film/color/kodak-professional-portra-400-film/516
+- **Ektar 100** — high saturation, ultra-vivid color, and exceptional sharpness.
+  Reference: https://www.kodakprofessional.com/photographers/film/color/filme-kodak-professional-ektar-100/530
+
+Kodak, Portra, Ektar, and Vision are trademarks of their respective owners.
+Their names are used descriptively. This project is not affiliated with or
+endorsed by Kodak.
diff --git b/assets/luts/kodak/README.md a/assets/luts/kodak/README.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..b888e2fa54c775f57840cb38b243c6d796e239a5
--- /dev/null
+++ a/assets/luts/kodak/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,13 @@
+# Film LUTs
+
+UVSR includes three original, Kodak-inspired looks generated specifically for
+its AgX Base-space pipeline. They are simulations, not official Kodak LUTs.
+
+Additional licensed 3D `.cube` LUT files can be placed in this directory before
+rebuilding UVSR. Valid LUTs are discovered at startup and appear in the
+Tonemapper section.
+
+UVSR supports `LUT_3D_SIZE`, `DOMAIN_MIN`, and `DOMAIN_MAX`. One-dimensional
+LUTs and combined 1D/3D files are intentionally unsupported.
+
+See `NOTICE.md` for look references and trademark information.
